    </caption>
  </mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="customizing-the-context-pane"><title>Customizing the Context pane</title> 
<para>At the bottom of the <emphasis>Context</emphasis> pane are four buttons for the default applets. On the right of these buttons you see <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref="Icon-configure.png" format="PNG"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject>, clicking on it will show <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref="Icon-application-exit.png" format="PNG"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> allowing you to remove these applets. Click the applets to add them to the pane. Drag the labeled buttons to re-order the applets you have, and click <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata fileref="Icon-configure.png" format="PNG"/> </imageobject> </inlinemediaobject> again to save your selections.
</para>
<para>This makes the <emphasis>Context</emphasis> pane extremely flexible, maximizing the possibility of a custom display that fits your preferences. More <link linkend="the-context-pane">here</link>.
