<sect2 id="get-tags-from-musicbrainz"><title>Get Tags from MusicBrainz</title> 
<para>&amarok; 2.8 has the ability to guess tags from the <guilabel>MusicBrainz</guilabel> database. Click the <guilabel>Get Tags from MusicBrainz</guilabel>, wait a moment for the database to be searched for matches, and then <guilabel>Update Tags</guilabel>, or <guilabel>Cancel</guilabel>.
</para>
<para>If you have the packages <emphasis>libofa</emphasis> and <emphasis>ffmpeg</emphasis> installed, and &amarok; is compiled with them, <guilabel>Musicbrainz</guilabel> will be able to use <quote>fingerprinting</quote> (the <emphasis>MusicDNS</emphasis> service) to search for albums and tracks without good filenames or existing tags.
