<chapter id="keybinding-reference"><title>Keybinding Reference</title> 
<sect1 id="keyboard-shortcuts"><title>Keyboard Shortcuts</title> 
<para>Keyboard shortcuts let you quickly access &amarok;<command>'s</command> power. Change the shortcuts using <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure Shortcuts...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>.
</para>
<para>
<screenshot>
<screeninfo></screeninfo>
  <mediaobject>
    <imageobject>
      <imagedata fileref="amarok24_settingsmenu.png" format="PNG"/>
    </imageobject>
    <textobject>
      <phrase></phrase>
    </textobject>
  </mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>
<para>Shortcuts are divided into two groups:
</para>
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><link linkend="kde-global-shortcuts">Global Shortcuts</link>&nbsp;</para></listitem>
<listitem><para><link linkend="amarok-shortcuts">Amarok Shortcuts</link>&nbsp;</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="control-from-console"><title>Control from Console</title> 
<para>To control &amarok; from the console, type <userinput>amarok --help-all</userinput> for a current complete list of available commands.
</para>
<sect2 id="kde-global-shortcuts"><title>KDE Global Shortcuts</title> 
<para><emphasis>Global Shortcuts</emphasis> are KDE's control key combinations. Use them to control &amarok; from the keyboard as an alternative to using the mouse.
</para>
<sect3 id="default-global-shortcuts"><title>Default Global Shortcuts</title> 
<para>
